        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/chiucs123/{size}/49854_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-12-06T17:09:16.719Z",
        "cooked": "<p>New group permission to prevent non-admin users to delete messages or set the maximum allowed time to do so.</p>\n<p><strong>Background</strong><br>\nSometimes there are cases where a data-sensitive discussion requires time-sensitive non-repudiation on the sender messages, however since users are allowed to delete messages for quite a while, it makes necessary information sometimes disappear too early if the user did take advantage of it. If group members need to wait that long to consider a message committed, it‚Äôll become an efficiency issue. Therefore a configurable group-specific deletion allowance or permission settings to turn that off would be great.</p>\n<p><strong>Advantages</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Group admins can adjust this time span according to the group‚Äôs needs.</li>\n<li>Information can be transparent to group members with a hint text above the message typing box.</li>\n<li>Prevents the case where Telegram groups can have everything deleted leaving people out of context.</li>\n<li>Having a time range setting can serve as a balance to user privacy and preserving context.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Concerns</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Users who shares content may find themselves unable to remove the content if they change their mind after (which also valid before suggested change).</li>\n<li>Users who are committed to a deletion period may result in a shortened time window if the group admin changes the setting to a shorter period. (Can be mitigated by having message-specific delete expiry - at the expense of additional metadata attached to the message.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Implementation</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Similar to disappearing messages under group settings.</li>\n<li>An additional permission settings to allow who can change the time, or disable the delete message function.</li>\n</ol>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2024-12-06T17:09:16.719Z",
