        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/{size}/34172_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-12-07T01:36:52.374Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This sounds like an existing feature request:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"7024\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/f14d63/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/make-disappearing-messages-work-per-message-not-per-conversation/7024\">Make disappearing messages work per message, not per conversation</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    This is a request to change how disappearing messages work, from conversational to per message. \nI may not have the most articulate response, but I believe there is a gap I noticed recently with the typing messages kind of potential issue of unwanted change in disappearing messages. \nWhen you are typing a message The other party sees the typing indicator, I can be malicious and change the disappearing messages timer prior to them hitting enter, not leaving them with enough time to react to chang‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
