        "created_at": "2024-12-07T11:02:38.699Z",
        "cooked": "<p>i think this is a separate request. if i understand the request correctly, they are asking for the admin to have more control over if and when someone may use the ‚Äúdelete for everyone‚Äù feature on their own messages in a group chat.<br>\nso for example, an admin can decide that rather than the <a href=\"https://signal.miraheze.org/wiki/Delete_for_everyone#Time_thresholds\">one day threshold</a> that is currently globally enforced, an admin may decide that users only have 2 hours, or that they can‚Äôt delete at all, or that they‚Äôre actually fine with people having a week to delete messages.<br>\nam i right in my understanding of your request, <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/chiucs123\">@chiucs123</a> ?</p>",
