        "created_at": "2024-12-07T11:14:10.449Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi Avitus &amp; Talya,</p>\n<p>Thank you for joining the discussion. I think my request is separate because the focus is to preserve the message for the right time rather than to make it disappear by default, but the idea for keeping track of per-message/conversation is similar.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote group-top_contributors\" data-username=\"rassilon1963\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"65293\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/48/31625_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> rassilon1963:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>am i right in my understanding of your request, <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/chiucs123\">@chiucs123</a> ?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes, indeed, we would like to have the ability to keep messages until after a said period of time. Whether to have the message disappear after is the other topic.</p>\n<p>Sometimes one day is too long when the matter at hand is something within the hours, but I guess it makes sense if general public is considered.</p>",
